Title: Human Reaction Time Cognitive Experiment

Introduction: Reaction time measures how quickly a person responds to a stimulus. It reflects how the brain processes sensory information and produces motor actions.

Methodology: Participants completed a reaction time test using an online tool. Two conditions were tested: normal environment and distraction with background music.

Data Collection

Twenty trials were recorded for each condition.

Results

Average reaction time in the normal condition was approximately 243 ms.
Average reaction time in the distraction condition was approximately 307 ms.

Conclusion

Reaction time increased during distraction, indicating that divided attention slows sensorimotor responses.
